  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "To simplify the presentation we could implement index wrap-around for vectors. That is, `vector[i]` would be equivalent to `vector[i % len(vector)]`. This would shorten about 20 lines, and potentially improve readability. Examples below:\r\n\r\n* `state.latest_block_roots[slot % SLOTS_PER_HISTORICAL_ROOT]` => `state.latest_block_roots[slot]`\r\n* `state.latest_randao_mixes[epoch % LATEST_RANDAO_MIXES_LENGTH]` => `state.latest_randao_mixes[epoch]`\r\n* `state.latest_active_index_roots[epoch % LATEST_ACTIVE_INDEX_ROOTS_LENGTH]`\r\n* `state.latest_slashed_balances[current_epoch % LATEST_SLASHED_EXIT_LENGTH]`\r\n* `state.latest_state_roots[state.slot % SLOTS_PER_HISTORICAL_ROOT]`",
